


scsi_initialise(3)     Transtech SCSI TRAM     scsi_initialise(3)



NAME
     scsi_initialise - Initialise SCSI TRAM

SYNOPSIS
     #include <scsi.h>

     extern int scsi_id;

     int scsi_initialise( void );

DESCRIPTION
     The function scsi_initialise initialises the Transtech  SCSI
     TRAM.   It also sets the global variable scsi_id to the SCSI
     id of the TRAM.

RETURN VALUE
     Returns the SCSI id of the TRAM  on  successful  initialisa-
     tion.  On error returns a negative integer.





































